A man has died and three others have been injured after a motorcycle collided with a group of pedestrians in southeast London. Emergency services were called to the scene on Plumstead Road in Woolwich at around 7.30pm. The police, London Ambulance Service and the Air Ambulance all attended. The man died at the scene, and the three other people involved were taken to hospital. Got a story? Get in touch with our news team by emailing us at webnews@metro.co.uk. Or you can submit your videos and pictures here. For more stories like this, check ourÂ news page. Follow Metro.co.uk on Twitter and Facebook for the latest news updates. You can now also get Metro.co.uk articles sent straight to your device. Sign up for our daily push alerts here.